name: MOBO Awards 2025
summary: The MOBO Awards 2025 was a star-studded event that celebrated the best in music of African and Caribbean descent. Bashy was the biggest winner of the night, taking home the award for Best Album after a 15-year hiatus. Central Cee made history by becoming the first artist to win four awards in a single night. Other winners included Darkoo, Odeal, and Vybz Kartel, who was honored with the MOBO Impact Award. The ceremony was held in Newcastle for the first time and featured performances from some of the biggest names in music.

Bayern's Davies was the hero for the German champions, while Celtic's valiant effort was not enough to overcome the aggregate deficit.

name: Rick Buckler
summary: Rick Buckler, the drummer for the influential British punk rock band The Jam, passed away at the age of 69 after a brief illness. The news sparked tributes from former bandmates Paul Weller and Bruce Foxton, who praised his contributions to the band. The Jam was known for its energetic live performances and timeless hits like "Going Underground" and "That's Entertainment." Buckler's drumming played a vital role in shaping the band's sound, and he was particularly proud of maintaining the core elements that defined The Jam's music.

name: Premium Bonds prize fund rate cut
summary: National Savings & Investments (NS&I) has cut the interest rate on its Premium Bonds from 4% to 3.8% effective from April. Consequently, there will be fewer high-value prizes available in the monthly draws. Customers with Premium Bonds are advised to consider their options and explore alternative savings accounts that may offer more competitive returns. The move has raised concerns among savers about the overall attractiveness of Premium Bonds, which have traditionally been popular due to their tax-free prizes. However, NS&I maintains that the chances of winning remain the same, and it encourages savers to hold on to their bonds.

name: Atalanta vs Club Brugge
summary: In the UEFA Champions League, Club Brugge emerged victorious over Atalanta in both legs of their knockout matchup. In the first leg, Club Brugge secured a vital 2-1 away win, courtesy of a late penalty kick. The second leg saw Club Brugge further extend their lead, prevailing 3-1 at home. As a result, Club Brugge advanced to the last 16 of the prestigious European competition.
